ks. These tunnels go as far as 1 m deep. Average clutch size 3 to 5 eggs. Habitat and conservation status It inhabits open country and clearings adjacent to forested areas, including over scrub and cogon fields, using dead trees and telephone wires as perches. The IUCN Red List has assessed this bird as least-concern species as it is common and is able to tolerate open habitat. References", "shortSummary": "The rufous-crowned bee-eater (Merops americanus) is a species of bird in the family Meropidae. It is endemic to the Philippines, where it i…", "locations": ["新大陸"], "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3b/Rufous-crowned_Bee-eater%2C_Subic_Bay%2C_Luzon_1.jpg/960px-Rufous-crowned_Bee-eater%2C_Subic_Bay%2C_Luzon_1.jpg", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-merops", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-merops-americanus", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-merops", "species": "taxonomy-species-merops-americanus"}, "expandable": true, "x": 15.81, "y": -106.67, "z": 646.56}, {"id": "taxonomy-genus-merops", "name": "Merops", "latinName": "Merops", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "genus", "summary": "Merops（Merops）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联27种鸟类，如Black-headed bee-eater、Red-throated bee-eater、Somali bee-eater等27种鸟类。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 27, "x": 271.44, "y": 354.3, "z": 44.94}], "links": [{"key": "bird-rufous-crowned-bee-eater-f70c61ae__belongs_to_species__taxonomy-species-merops-americanus", "source": "bird-rufous-crowned-bee-eater-f70c61ae", "target": "taxonomy-species-merops-americanus", "relation": "belongs_to_species", "label": "属于种", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 中的种字段补充。"}, {"key": "taxonomy-species-merops-americanus__belongs_to_genus__taxonomy-genus-merops", "source": "taxonomy-species-merops-americanus", "target"